column5: Wondering if we can still bring hashbrowns, and frozen processed potatoes

I have always thought that commercially packaged potatoes were permitted. Whether it be frozen or fresh in bags from the grocery store, no problems. Potatoes grown in your backyard garden were not permitted. In all the years we have gone to Canada, never has the border guard asked us about our food suffs.
There biggest concern now is a worm n salted minnow!
